1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,568
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,568 --> 00:00:03,036
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:09,397 --> 00:00:11,231
The analysis results show that...

4
00:00:11,231 --> 00:00:13,113
the child in Madam's pendant photo
is presumed...

5
00:00:13,297 --> 00:00:15,849
to be the same person as the child
in the photo you saw last time.

6
00:00:16,323 --> 00:00:17,370
Is that really true?

7
00:00:17,370 --> 00:00:19,390
Yes. We confirmed
that she was adopted and sent to France...

8
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:21,764
the year after you were separated.

9
00:00:21,764 --> 00:00:24,858
France?
Then does that mean she's in France now?

10
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:26,872
No. Unfortunately,

11
00:00:27,507 --> 00:00:29,340
she was abandoned
by her adoptive family after five years...

12
00:00:29,340 --> 00:00:30,965
and sent back to Korea.

13
00:00:31,507 --> 00:00:32,973
After that, her whereabouts disappeared.

14
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:37,640
What do you mean,
her whereabouts disappeared?

15
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:40,441
At the time, overseas adoption agencies
weren't well organized,

16
00:00:40,893 --> 00:00:43,277
and records were handwritten
instead of digitized,

17
00:00:44,087 --> 00:00:45,445
so it seems information
may have been lost...

18
00:00:45,445 --> 00:00:48,173
or recorded incorrectly
during the process.

19
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:50,273
Darn it.

20
00:00:50,273 --> 00:00:52,953
For now, we've requested
an age progression analysis...

21
00:00:53,505 --> 00:00:55,439
to estimate her current appearance
from old photos.

22
00:00:55,779 --> 00:00:58,279
We're also tracing several other leads,

23
00:00:58,807 --> 00:00:59,907
so please wait a little longer.

24
00:00:59,907 --> 00:01:02,363
Of course I'll wait.

25
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:05,273
We searched for decades
without finding a single trace of her.

26
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:07,407
The fact that we found this much already
means a lot.

27
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:10,938
- Please keep up the good work.
- Yes, Chairman.

28
00:01:22,132 --> 00:01:24,699
Father, I'm heading to work.

29
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,321
All right. Have a good day, CEO Ko.

30
00:01:38,573 --> 00:01:39,900
Yeah, let's see...

31
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:42,269
how long that confidence lasts.

32
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:20,207
Wait, where did this go?

33
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,280
Where could it have...

34
00:02:24,272 --> 00:02:25,272
No way...

35
00:02:27,973 --> 00:02:28,973
Mother,

36
00:02:30,219 --> 00:02:32,185
would you like
to have some morning coffee with me?

37
00:02:34,826 --> 00:02:35,922
What's wrong, Mother?

38
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:39,593
So you really went through with it?
Did you really?

39
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:43,397
Sorry? What are you talking about?

40
00:02:43,907 --> 00:02:45,599
Where's the photo that was inside this?

41
00:02:46,707 --> 00:02:47,901
Bring it to me right now.

42
00:02:48,273 --> 00:02:50,207
What? What photo?

43
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:53,473
There was a photo inside that?

44
00:02:53,593 --> 00:02:54,860
I said bring it to me right now!

45
00:03:00,812 --> 00:03:03,183
Su Jeong, leave us alone for a moment.

46
00:03:03,899 --> 00:03:04,899
Yes.

47
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,494
Here's the photo.

48
00:03:16,507 --> 00:03:19,333
Honey...

49
00:03:22,025 --> 00:03:24,504
I'm sorry for touching it
without telling you,

50
00:03:25,092 --> 00:03:29,142
but I've been trying
to find Yeon Sun again lately.

51
00:03:30,699 --> 00:03:33,313
We searched for decades...

52
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:37,150
without finding any trace of her.
So how can you find her now?

53
00:03:38,099 --> 00:03:39,353
I promised you, didn't I?

54
00:03:40,507 --> 00:03:41,640
I promised to never leave you alone...

55
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:46,126
and die first.

56
00:03:47,332 --> 00:03:49,262
Honey...

57
00:03:51,692 --> 00:03:55,380
Please just know...

58
00:03:55,380 --> 00:03:56,937
that I still haven't let go...

59
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:01,174
of my last thread of hope.

60
00:04:17,552 --> 00:04:18,552
Yeon Sun.

61
00:04:20,432 --> 00:04:22,232
Mom will come back for you soon.

62
00:04:22,946 --> 00:04:25,599
Wait here for ten nights, no...

63
00:04:26,302 --> 00:04:28,869
Wait for 20 nights, okay?

64
00:04:29,112 --> 00:04:33,173
Really?
You really will come back for me, right?

65
00:04:34,292 --> 00:04:37,092
Of course. It's just for a little while.

66
00:04:38,407 --> 00:04:42,607
I can't live even a single day
without you, Yeon Sun.

67
00:04:46,499 --> 00:04:48,388
Here.

68
00:04:49,740 --> 00:04:53,307
You have my photo, and I have your photo.

69
00:04:54,073 --> 00:04:55,796
If you wear this necklace,

70
00:04:57,220 --> 00:05:00,467
it means we're always together, okay?

71
00:05:03,472 --> 00:05:05,538
Mom, you have to come back.

72
00:05:05,866 --> 00:05:08,041
You have to come back for me.

73
00:05:08,498 --> 00:05:13,379
Promise me you'll eat well, sleep well,

74
00:05:14,307 --> 00:05:15,983
and not cry until I come back.

75
00:05:16,552 --> 00:05:18,384
Okay, I promise.

76
00:05:24,091 --> 00:05:25,091
I'm sorry.

77
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:29,863
I'm sorry I can't take you with me.

78
00:05:31,007 --> 00:05:33,240
It's okay. You'll come back soon.

79
00:05:35,373 --> 00:05:37,640
Mom, you smell so nice.

80
00:05:42,397 --> 00:05:43,507
My smell?

81
00:05:46,906 --> 00:05:48,048
Then...

82
00:05:49,207 --> 00:05:50,483
Keep this.

83
00:05:50,907 --> 00:05:55,107
Whenever you miss my scent,
open this, okay?

84
00:05:59,392 --> 00:06:02,392
As soon as I get my parents' permission,
we'll come back for her right away.

85
00:06:02,959 --> 00:06:04,826
Please take good care of her until then.

86
00:06:05,846 --> 00:06:07,700
You worry too much.

87
00:06:07,907 --> 00:06:10,440
It's not like I don't know you,
Director Ko Kang Su.

88
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:14,208
That's right. Don't worry too much.

89
00:06:14,739 --> 00:06:16,607
I'll treasure her...

90
00:06:16,607 --> 00:06:18,940
like she's my own daughter.

91
00:06:19,539 --> 00:06:20,539
Thank you.

92
00:06:28,445 --> 00:06:29,445
Yeon Sun.

93
00:06:33,673 --> 00:06:36,897
I will come back with your mom to get you.

94
00:06:37,632 --> 00:06:38,632
Just wait a little.

95
00:06:42,059 --> 00:06:44,826
Did it hurt a lot, Mister?

96
00:06:46,719 --> 00:06:47,752
I'm sorry.

97
00:06:48,473 --> 00:06:51,173
No. It didn't hurt at all.

98
00:06:52,473 --> 00:06:56,516
I'm just so happy
that you grew up healthy.

99
00:06:57,773 --> 00:06:58,807
Don't be sorry.

100
00:07:04,645 --> 00:07:05,979
Don't cry, Mom.

101
00:07:06,963 --> 00:07:09,496
I can wait well.

102
00:07:10,359 --> 00:07:14,225
I'll eat well, sleep well,

103
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:15,826
and never cry.

104
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:19,873
If I can't sleep,
I can just sing "Wild Rose."

105
00:07:23,807 --> 00:07:24,807
All right.

106
00:07:26,540 --> 00:07:28,615
You're a good girl, my Yeon Sun.

107
00:07:31,653 --> 00:07:33,787
Don't go anywhere, and wait here.

108
00:07:34,940 --> 00:07:37,407
Mom will come back for you soon.

109
00:07:39,033 --> 00:07:40,900
- Please come out quickly.
- Yes.

110
00:07:44,407 --> 00:07:46,340
Yeong Hwa, let's go.

111
00:07:49,104 --> 00:07:50,537
You have to wait here.

112
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:54,173
Please hurry out.

113
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:55,432
Yes, we're coming.

114
00:08:06,666 --> 00:08:07,700
I'm sorry.

115
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:12,372
I'm so sorry for breaking our promise,

116
00:08:12,373 --> 00:08:13,640
Yeon Sun.

117
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:26,906
(Cho Eun Nim)

118
00:08:31,227 --> 00:08:32,613
It feels like it was just yesterday...

119
00:08:33,986 --> 00:08:37,686
when I dressed them in this
and couldn't stop looking at them.

120
00:08:41,073 --> 00:08:42,289
Yeah.

121
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:46,593
Just because I gave birth to them
and raised them,

122
00:08:47,140 --> 00:08:50,664
it's selfish to expect them
to live the lives I want for them.

123
00:09:22,173 --> 00:09:24,007
Is that why you left me too?

124
00:09:25,873 --> 00:09:27,534
So I could live my life my own way?

125
00:09:46,792 --> 00:09:47,859
Good morning, Mom.

126
00:09:53,439 --> 00:09:54,739
Mom, taste this for me.

127
00:09:55,373 --> 00:09:57,397
No matter how much I try it, I can't tell.

128
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,207
Take it away.

129
00:10:02,573 --> 00:10:05,507
Why? I made it because I thought
your stomach might be hurting.

130
00:10:05,807 --> 00:10:07,673
It's the first dish I've ever made.

131
00:10:08,166 --> 00:10:10,276
Let's eat together, Mom. Please?

132
00:10:10,766 --> 00:10:13,413
First you hurt me, and now you're trying
to comfort me? Eat it yourself.

133
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:16,540
Mom, please. I'm really sorry, okay?

134
00:10:16,807 --> 00:10:18,485
But I really had no choice.

135
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:20,113
Fine.

136
00:10:20,113 --> 00:10:23,490
You all want to live your own lives,
so how can I stop you?

137
00:10:26,907 --> 00:10:28,328
Come this way.

138
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:35,149
Presenting...

139
00:10:35,149 --> 00:10:37,872
Cho Eun Nim's very first bean sprout soup.

140
00:10:40,273 --> 00:10:43,877
But is that blood phobia thing
really hard to cure?

141
00:10:43,877 --> 00:10:45,378
Why? If it's cured, then what?

142
00:10:45,545 --> 00:10:47,407
I mean, if it's making you suffer,

143
00:10:47,407 --> 00:10:49,583
maybe you should go to a hospital
and get treatment.

144
00:10:50,013 --> 00:10:52,513
I don't know
how this will sound to you, Mom,

145
00:10:53,038 --> 00:10:55,538
but I think
I've mostly overcome it mentally now.

146
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,040
What?

147
00:10:57,286 --> 00:10:58,952
The main character in my novel
is actually me.

148
00:10:59,107 --> 00:11:00,860
But even when blood is gushing everywhere,

149
00:11:00,861 --> 00:11:02,820
she calmly stops the bleeding,
performs surgery,

150
00:11:02,821 --> 00:11:04,497
and saves dying patients.

151
00:11:05,073 --> 00:11:07,133
But while writing it,

152
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:09,035
at some point,
blood stopped being so scary.

153
00:11:09,607 --> 00:11:12,473
Before, even thinking about it
made me nauseous and want to throw up.

154
00:11:13,973 --> 00:11:16,080
Mom,
I think becoming a web novel writer...

155
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:18,307
was really the right choice for me,
don't you?

156
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:21,180
Look at you being all happy.

157
00:11:22,955 --> 00:11:26,156
Wait. If you think
you've overcome it psychologically...

158
00:11:26,156 --> 00:11:29,622
Why? Are you going to tell me
to go back to school?

159
00:11:29,906 --> 00:11:31,673
Whether it's returning or reenrolling,

160
00:11:31,973 --> 00:11:34,194
even if you postpone the licensing exam,

161
00:11:34,773 --> 00:11:38,040
you should at least get your diploma.

162
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:40,873
Mom,
please let go of that expectation now.

163
00:11:41,407 --> 00:11:44,007
I'm confident I can make you proud
even as a web novel writer.

164
00:11:44,712 --> 00:11:47,373
When you have time,
please read my novel at least once, okay?

165
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:50,399
Forget it. I already have a headache.

166
00:11:50,399 --> 00:11:51,978
I don't have time
to read something like that.

167
00:11:58,046 --> 00:11:59,273
What is this? It's salty.

168
00:11:59,273 --> 00:12:00,620
What? Is it really that salty?

169
00:12:06,359 --> 00:12:07,640
(Kangsu Construction)

170
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,429
If you had something to say,
you could've said it at home.

171
00:12:09,429 --> 00:12:10,697
Why did you call me to the office?

172
00:12:11,993 --> 00:12:15,268
I just had something a little confidential
to talk about.

173
00:12:16,707 --> 00:12:19,139
By the way, is my father...

174
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:21,274
looking for someone these days?

175
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:22,907
Looking for someone?

176
00:12:23,705 --> 00:12:26,940
Well, the Chairman's always been looking
for lots of people.

177
00:12:26,940 --> 00:12:29,115
- Lots of people? Like who?
- Let's see.

178
00:12:30,506 --> 00:12:34,487
Back in 1988,
when we were building Kangsu Apartments,

179
00:12:34,692 --> 00:12:37,990
there was a very diligent employee,
Assistant Manager Park.

180
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:42,148
He got sick and returned to his hometown,
and about ten years passed.

181
00:12:43,698 --> 00:12:47,299
The Chairman somehow found him
and brought him back.

182
00:12:48,678 --> 00:12:50,140
You know the executive director, right?

183
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,604
- That man is actually...
- Stop.

184
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:54,207
Stop. Please stop right there.

185
00:12:54,779 --> 00:12:57,379
No, not that. I heard Father's been...

186
00:12:57,979 --> 00:13:00,213
looking for some child lately.

187
00:13:00,512 --> 00:13:01,914
A child? What child?

188
00:13:02,340 --> 00:13:03,340
That...

189
00:13:05,226 --> 00:13:06,752
That child.

190
00:13:08,226 --> 00:13:10,757
"That child?" What kind of child?

191
00:13:11,591 --> 00:13:12,591
How would I know?

192
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:15,159
That's why I'm asking you right now.

193
00:13:16,807 --> 00:13:18,007
I don't really know either.

194
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:21,768
If you're that curious,
ask the Chairman directly.

195
00:13:22,026 --> 00:13:23,236
Seriously...

196
00:13:24,346 --> 00:13:25,746
If you're done here, I'll get going.

197
00:13:30,326 --> 00:13:33,279
Does he really not know,
or is he pretending not to know?

198
00:13:33,513 --> 00:13:35,715
He's as sly as a fox.

199
00:13:49,888 --> 00:13:51,706
- Are you busy?
- Not at all.

200
00:13:51,707 --> 00:13:52,932
What brings you here?

201
00:13:53,889 --> 00:13:55,599
CEO Ko called me over for a bit.

202
00:13:55,599 --> 00:13:56,769
I see.

203
00:13:59,379 --> 00:14:02,475
About that.
The person the Chairman's looking for.

204
00:14:04,153 --> 00:14:05,378
Any progress?

205
00:14:05,932 --> 00:14:06,932
Excuse me?

206
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:09,640
So you know about it?

207
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:12,685
I told you. There's nothing I don't know.

208
00:14:13,821 --> 00:14:15,855
There's nothing in particular
for me to say.

209
00:14:16,860 --> 00:14:20,827
I guess that's why
the Chairman trusts you so much, Mr. Seo.

210
00:14:21,932 --> 00:14:24,997
Did CEO Ko ask about the person
the Chairman is searching for?

211
00:14:25,807 --> 00:14:28,368
I don't really have anything
to say either.

212
00:14:29,192 --> 00:14:33,473
Keeping things tightly locked up...

213
00:14:33,699 --> 00:14:35,942
is the most basic duty
of an assistant, isn't it?

214
00:14:36,532 --> 00:14:37,643
Yes.

215
00:14:37,807 --> 00:14:40,413
By the way, does Seong Jun...

216
00:14:40,679 --> 00:14:43,550
plan to become CEO Ko's assistant or not?

217
00:14:43,772 --> 00:14:45,885
It's been quite a while
since the offer was made.

218
00:14:47,212 --> 00:14:48,287
I'm not sure...

219
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,507
You're so discreet.

220
00:14:52,405 --> 00:14:54,627
Too discreet.

221
00:14:57,592 --> 00:15:00,199
I uploaded the presentation materials,
Team Manager. Please check them.

222
00:15:00,473 --> 00:15:01,740
Okay. Good work.

223
00:15:02,373 --> 00:15:04,807
Team Manager, before the presentation,

224
00:15:04,807 --> 00:15:07,040
shouldn't we do a rehearsal?

225
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:09,409
A rehearsal?

226
00:15:10,198 --> 00:15:11,356
Ms. Cho.

227
00:15:11,740 --> 00:15:15,115
He has swept multiple
world-class architectural competitions...

228
00:15:15,307 --> 00:15:18,284
and even won Young Architect of the Year.
Do you think he needs to rehearse?

229
00:15:18,506 --> 00:15:21,287
No, I think it's a good idea.
Let's do it tonight.

230
00:15:22,907 --> 00:15:25,458
Team Manager Ko,
the CEO wants to see you with me.

231
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:27,473
Right now? Okay.

232
00:15:29,073 --> 00:15:31,965
All right. D-day is next week.

233
00:15:31,965 --> 00:15:33,833
Please do your best until the very end.

234
00:15:34,107 --> 00:15:35,268
Well then, enjoy your lunches.

235
00:15:36,392 --> 00:15:38,104
It's already lunchtime.

236
00:15:38,566 --> 00:15:39,706
Manager Seo, let's go eat.

237
00:15:40,066 --> 00:15:41,933
I don't really feel like eating,
so you all go ahead.

238
00:15:42,547 --> 00:15:45,673
Again? Are you on a diet or something?

239
00:15:45,673 --> 00:15:48,981
No. I normally can't stomach food well
before something important.

240
00:15:48,981 --> 00:15:49,981
Okay.

241
00:15:50,432 --> 00:15:51,432
Come on, hurry up.

242
00:15:51,432 --> 00:15:53,352
If we're late,
the cafeteria line will get way too long.

243
00:16:01,365 --> 00:16:04,830
Manager Seo, do you have a moment?

244
00:16:12,474 --> 00:16:14,907
What is it? Why did you ask me
to come all the way up here?

245
00:16:15,607 --> 00:16:17,873
Whenever I feel frustrated or nervous,

246
00:16:17,873 --> 00:16:20,607
breathing deeply somewhere open like this
helps me calm down a bit.

247
00:16:21,106 --> 00:16:22,439
Try it like me.

248
00:16:30,286 --> 00:16:32,186
All right. So what did you want to say?

249
00:16:34,740 --> 00:16:38,198
You said before that I lack
the basics of professional life.

250
00:16:39,173 --> 00:16:40,766
At first, I thought you only said that...

251
00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:43,369
because of a misunderstanding
about me and the Team Manager,

252
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,873
but I don't think that's the case anymore.

253
00:16:46,525 --> 00:16:47,625
What makes you think that?

254
00:16:48,066 --> 00:16:51,272
I majored in engineering,
and the only work experience I have...

255
00:16:51,273 --> 00:16:53,212
is running a startup.

256
00:16:53,853 --> 00:16:55,519
I only get to meet
a limited number of people too.

257
00:16:57,066 --> 00:17:01,387
You were right. I really haven't had
proper workplace experience.

258
00:17:02,193 --> 00:17:03,760
I'll work on improving that from now on,

259
00:17:04,385 --> 00:17:07,593
especially so the Team Manager
won't get misunderstood...

260
00:17:07,973 --> 00:17:09,298
because of me.

261
00:17:10,607 --> 00:17:13,307
What I said before
was a little too emotional.

262
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:15,207
I was surprised...

263
00:17:15,207 --> 00:17:17,307
by how uninhibited you were
with your superior.

264
00:17:18,107 --> 00:17:19,572
Don't take it too much to heart.

265
00:17:20,707 --> 00:17:23,107
I'm not very perceptive,
and I can be a little eccentric.

266
00:17:23,907 --> 00:17:25,907
I've heard that a lot since I was young.

267
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,873
Whenever I get into something,

268
00:17:28,873 --> 00:17:31,473
I focus only on that
and ignore everything around me.

269
00:17:32,907 --> 00:17:35,640
That personality must be what created Joy.

270
00:17:36,373 --> 00:17:38,057
- Excuse me?
- I told you already.

271
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,807
Joy is an excellent program.

272
00:17:40,407 --> 00:17:43,273
Without ignoring everything around you
and focusing only on your own ideas,

273
00:17:43,273 --> 00:17:44,940
you probably couldn't have created Joy.

274
00:17:45,507 --> 00:17:46,873
Are you complimenting me right now...

275
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,507
There I go again.

276
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:53,540
It's okay.
The basic manners I asked you to keep...

277
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:54,740
weren't about something like that.

278
00:17:55,607 --> 00:17:56,607
Just act like you normally do.

279
00:17:57,393 --> 00:17:58,878
Yes, thank you.

280
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:03,249
And there's one last thing I want to say.

281
00:18:04,026 --> 00:18:07,273
I'm not working here...

282
00:18:07,273 --> 00:18:09,107
just to kill time for six months.

283
00:18:11,740 --> 00:18:13,859
I guess my words hurt you
more than I thought.

284
00:18:14,540 --> 00:18:15,762
Rather than me getting hurt,

285
00:18:16,140 --> 00:18:18,807
I just thought
I should make my intentions clear.

286
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:22,946
At first,
I accepted the internship offer...

287
00:18:22,946 --> 00:18:26,372
because I wanted to somehow get Joy back.
But not anymore.

288
00:18:27,407 --> 00:18:29,709
Incorporating Joy
into the retirement community project...

289
00:18:30,009 --> 00:18:32,440
makes it feel like
I'm getting one step closer...

290
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:34,240
to the dream I originally had
when I first developed Joy.

291
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:38,251
I'm really giving this my all.

292
00:18:38,873 --> 00:18:40,673
I'll prove it in the competition.

293
00:18:41,073 --> 00:18:42,722
I'm confident that I'll win.

294
00:18:43,572 --> 00:18:46,772
Really? That's a problem.
Because I'm not confident about losing.

295
00:18:47,173 --> 00:18:50,707
Excuse me? Then will it end in a draw?

296
00:18:51,307 --> 00:18:53,673
What do we do then?
Should there be a redemption match?

297
00:18:56,507 --> 00:18:59,041
I didn't mean that I'd dare compete
against you, Manager Seo.

298
00:18:59,407 --> 00:19:02,240
I just meant that I'll do my best
in the role I've been given.

299
00:19:04,373 --> 00:19:06,740
You really have a talent...

300
00:19:06,740 --> 00:19:08,273
for making people feel embarrassed.

301
00:19:08,607 --> 00:19:12,507
Excuse me? Did I do something wrong again?

302
00:19:12,852 --> 00:19:14,353
No, that's not what I meant.

303
00:19:15,590 --> 00:19:17,957
Let's both do our best
in our respective positions.

304
00:19:19,007 --> 00:19:20,673
Yes. I'll work hard.

305
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:29,080
The Chairman has also decided to join
the judges' panel for the competition.

306
00:19:29,893 --> 00:19:31,103
That's what I had to tell you.

307
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,506
I assumed he would.

308
00:19:35,140 --> 00:19:37,743
But up until now,

309
00:19:37,743 --> 00:19:39,245
why hasn't Team Two requested any support?

310
00:19:39,245 --> 00:19:42,748
For now,
we don't particularly need any support.

311
00:19:43,399 --> 00:19:45,733
I see. Still,
so the Chairman won't misunderstand...

312
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:48,973
and think we only poured resources
into Team One,

313
00:19:48,973 --> 00:19:50,222
do it properly.

314
00:19:50,222 --> 00:19:51,424
Yes, understood.

315
00:19:52,857 --> 00:19:55,357
Still, since we're all here,
how about we have lunch together?

316
00:19:55,357 --> 00:19:58,364
No. He and I still have something
to discuss separately.

317
00:20:00,707 --> 00:20:02,001
- Then...
- All right.

318
00:20:05,699 --> 00:20:07,173
- Really?
- Yeah.

319
00:20:07,973 --> 00:20:10,576
But even if I'm just working
for a service company,

320
00:20:10,576 --> 00:20:12,836
I still have to wait
until my replacement comes,

321
00:20:12,837 --> 00:20:14,107
so it could take a few days.

322
00:20:14,812 --> 00:20:16,649
That's nothing.

323
00:20:18,866 --> 00:20:22,288
Thinking that you'll be by my side now
makes me feel really reassured.

324
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:26,726
And make sure you set an adequate salary
for someone with experience.

325
00:20:28,312 --> 00:20:30,462
That way, I can feel at ease.

326
00:20:31,172 --> 00:20:32,305
Seriously, you.

327
00:20:32,986 --> 00:20:34,266
If it were anyone else,

328
00:20:34,266 --> 00:20:36,640
they'd still be begging
for a higher salary.

329
00:20:37,973 --> 00:20:42,041
I guess this is exactly
why I like you so much.

330
00:20:42,577 --> 00:20:44,477
Hey, want to go grab lunch?

331
00:20:45,166 --> 00:20:47,046
No, I still have work to finish.

332
00:20:47,407 --> 00:20:49,182
Really? Then how about tonight?

333
00:20:49,707 --> 00:20:51,717
Want to grab a drink with Gwon Sik?

334
00:20:53,107 --> 00:20:54,654
This is seriously driving me crazy.

335
00:20:55,053 --> 00:20:58,124
I'm dying to see the look
on Gwon Sik's face...

336
00:20:58,361 --> 00:21:01,594
when he finds out
you're becoming my secretary.

337
00:21:04,706 --> 00:21:07,399
- I'm leaving now.
- Okay.

338
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,740
Game over. That's it.

339
00:21:16,266 --> 00:21:19,178
Seo Gwon Sik.

340
00:21:19,178 --> 00:21:21,333
You're a kite with a snapped string now,
you punk.

341
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:22,333
Seo Gwon Sik.

342
00:21:24,507 --> 00:21:26,973
You haven't requested support
even once until now.

343
00:21:27,307 --> 00:21:28,954
Are you really doing your best?

344
00:21:29,340 --> 00:21:32,607
Of course. I'm more serious
about this project than anyone else.

345
00:21:33,473 --> 00:21:36,229
So you really intend to beat me...

346
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:38,731
and become the successor of Kangsu Group?

347
00:21:39,386 --> 00:21:43,202
Honestly, being the successor
isn't that important to me.

348
00:21:43,406 --> 00:21:45,238
Then what is important to you?

349
00:21:45,745 --> 00:21:48,307
Grandfather's dream
that brought Kangsu Construction this far.

350
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:51,644
And my father's dream.

351
00:21:54,599 --> 00:21:57,283
Once the competition ends,
you're going back to the U.S., right?

352
00:21:57,707 --> 00:21:59,519
Do you hate having me here that much?

353
00:21:59,519 --> 00:22:01,888
Of course I do. I completely,
absolutely can't stand it, you punk.

354
00:22:02,078 --> 00:22:06,325
Being so blunt about your feelings
really is your trademark.

355
00:22:07,507 --> 00:22:08,961
I know because I've been through it.

356
00:22:09,312 --> 00:22:12,431
When someone's right in front of you,
your heart can never move on.

357
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,500
It's torture.

358
00:22:15,025 --> 00:22:16,668
Sounds like you're talking
about Manager Seo.

359
00:22:17,540 --> 00:22:20,573
What should I do
to help you move past those feelings?

360
00:22:20,573 --> 00:22:21,841
There's no other way.

361
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:24,307
None other than you leaving
no matter what.

362
00:22:24,873 --> 00:22:26,145
There is one way.

363
00:22:26,999 --> 00:22:29,348
You and Ms. Cho Eun Ae
genuinely getting together...

364
00:22:29,753 --> 00:22:31,884
so Seung Ri gives up completely.

365
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,455
("The ER Witch")

366
00:22:38,666 --> 00:22:41,493
No matter how I look at it,
I'm the one who has to draw this.

367
00:22:42,212 --> 00:22:43,968
For a grand and profound world like this,

368
00:22:44,918 --> 00:22:46,198
I'm the perfect fit.

369
00:22:47,073 --> 00:22:48,340
You think I'm crazy?

370
00:22:48,340 --> 00:22:50,302
Why would I entrust my novel
to someone like you?

371
00:22:50,302 --> 00:22:52,607
If you hate it that much,

372
00:22:53,267 --> 00:22:55,074
we can just do meetings online...

373
00:22:55,573 --> 00:22:58,044
and not meet in person.
We don't have to meet.

374
00:22:58,391 --> 00:23:00,813
Forget it. I said no.

375
00:23:01,807 --> 00:23:04,350
Why does she hate me so much?

376
00:23:04,473 --> 00:23:07,787
I have to draw this. Seriously.

377
00:23:11,858 --> 00:23:13,692
Do you think the desk will break
from that?

378
00:23:14,653 --> 00:23:17,563
I'm going to exercise,
so make sure you eat lunch.

379
00:23:20,707 --> 00:23:22,969
Mom, I have a question.

380
00:23:23,647 --> 00:23:26,439
How exactly do you win someone's heart?

381
00:23:26,873 --> 00:23:28,975
Win someone's heart? Whose heart?

382
00:23:30,412 --> 00:23:32,645
- A girl's?
- Yeah, a girl's.

383
00:23:32,645 --> 00:23:34,313
- Is she pretty?
- Yeah, she's pretty.

384
00:23:36,198 --> 00:23:39,685
Could you answer a little more sincerely?

385
00:23:39,685 --> 00:23:43,856
I am asking sincerely right now.

386
00:23:44,273 --> 00:23:45,558
- Is she really pretty?
- Well...

387
00:23:46,285 --> 00:23:49,795
I guess she's pretty, but... She's cute.

388
00:23:52,298 --> 00:23:53,513
What am I even saying?

389
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:57,507
So she is pretty.

390
00:23:58,705 --> 00:24:01,940
Could it be that soulmate girl
you mentioned before?

391
00:24:03,112 --> 00:24:04,607
Chills. How did you know?

392
00:24:04,607 --> 00:24:08,214
Geez. First, just get close to her.

393
00:24:08,692 --> 00:24:10,248
Don't come on too strong.

394
00:24:10,540 --> 00:24:11,958
After you get close,

395
00:24:11,958 --> 00:24:14,587
watch carefully to see
whether she feels the same way about you,

396
00:24:14,873 --> 00:24:16,607
then pick the perfect moment to confess.

397
00:24:18,979 --> 00:24:21,154
Who said this was about dating?

398
00:24:21,154 --> 00:24:23,662
It's a collaboration. A collaboration.

399
00:24:23,662 --> 00:24:26,765
But if you two collaborate,
will the producer sign you?

400
00:24:27,326 --> 00:24:28,526
He told me to hold on tight.

401
00:24:29,207 --> 00:24:32,304
I have a feeling
that if I miss this chance,

402
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:33,539
I'll regret it for the rest of my life.

403
00:24:33,540 --> 00:24:36,738
If that's how you feel,
then show her your sincerity.

404
00:24:37,926 --> 00:24:42,155
Believe that if you truly want something,
it'll come true, okay?

405
00:24:42,673 --> 00:24:43,673
I'm leaving.

406
00:24:47,307 --> 00:24:48,487
My sincerity?

407
00:24:50,946 --> 00:24:53,113
How am I supposed to show that?

408
00:24:55,146 --> 00:24:56,240
Hello.

409
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,273
- Hello.
- Hello.

410
00:24:57,273 --> 00:24:59,999
You're here? Why's it been so long?

411
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:02,401
I had some family matters.

412
00:25:02,705 --> 00:25:04,972
From now on,
I'll come regularly and work hard.

413
00:25:09,207 --> 00:25:10,843
Have you been well, Minho's mother?

414
00:25:12,807 --> 00:25:13,879
You must've improved a lot.

415
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:18,840
Don't worry.
I probably won't be able to keep up.

416
00:25:19,140 --> 00:25:21,653
It's not like I'd covet that spot.

417
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,473
Who's worried?

418
00:25:26,540 --> 00:25:29,228
How do I completely crush
that woman's spirit?

419
00:25:30,532 --> 00:25:33,832
Oh là là, je pense, donc je suis.

420
00:25:35,607 --> 00:25:39,038
I knew you could dance well,
but your French is good too.

421
00:25:39,866 --> 00:25:41,632
What does that mean?

422
00:25:42,046 --> 00:25:43,746
Excuse me? The meaning?

423
00:25:44,707 --> 00:25:46,807
I'm curious too. Tell us.

424
00:25:47,407 --> 00:25:48,814
You majored in French literature, right?

425
00:25:49,107 --> 00:25:50,973
So you majored in French literature.

426
00:25:51,507 --> 00:25:54,120
No wonder you seem so elegant.

427
00:25:54,907 --> 00:25:57,256
"Je pense, donc je suis."

428
00:25:57,792 --> 00:26:01,059
It's a line from a famous poem
by the French poet Baudelaire.

429
00:26:01,343 --> 00:26:04,430
It means, "I exist, therefore I think."

430
00:26:04,708 --> 00:26:07,855
I suddenly had a lot on my mind
before class,

431
00:26:07,855 --> 00:26:09,067
so it came to me.

432
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:10,770
Oh là là.

433
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:14,440
Je pense, donc je suis.

434
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:17,840
"I think, therefore I am."

435
00:26:18,573 --> 00:26:21,907
That's not from Baudelaire.
It was said by the philosopher Descartes.

436
00:26:21,907 --> 00:26:23,582
What?

437
00:26:23,940 --> 00:26:25,551
That's unbelievable.

438
00:26:25,773 --> 00:26:28,840
A person has to exist first
in order to think.

439
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:30,856
How can thinking come before existing?

440
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:32,852
Why talk when you don't even know?

441
00:26:32,852 --> 00:26:34,019
She's right.

442
00:26:34,673 --> 00:26:37,273
"I think, therefore I am."

443
00:26:38,197 --> 00:26:42,507
That's not from a Baudelaire poem.
It's something Descartes said.

444
00:26:42,507 --> 00:26:45,871
Then did that Descartes guy
plagiarize Baudelaire?

445
00:26:46,325 --> 00:26:49,174
And existence comes before thought.

446
00:26:50,273 --> 00:26:51,677
What do you all think?

447
00:26:51,959 --> 00:26:53,265
- That's right.
- You're right.

448
00:26:55,507 --> 00:26:56,540
That's right.

449
00:26:59,693 --> 00:27:02,154
How are you so good at French,
Ms. Kang Yeon Ja?

450
00:27:02,459 --> 00:27:05,757
Please. It's just such a famous phrase.

451
00:27:06,140 --> 00:27:08,081
- Hello.
- Hello.

452
00:27:08,081 --> 00:27:09,395
Hello.

453
00:27:09,873 --> 00:27:11,873
- Ready?
- Yes.

454
00:27:11,873 --> 00:27:13,773
Shall we start energetically again today?

455
00:27:13,773 --> 00:27:14,934
- Yes!
- Yes!

456
00:27:28,740 --> 00:27:32,284
So what if you didn't know the meaning?
Why are you getting so worked up over it?

457
00:27:32,612 --> 00:27:34,319
It's not that I didn't know.

458
00:27:34,539 --> 00:27:37,872
Think about it.
Which comes first, existence or thought?

459
00:27:38,393 --> 00:27:41,627
And I'm telling you,
Descartes definitely plagiarized it.

460
00:27:42,807 --> 00:27:44,007
Okay, I get it.

461
00:27:44,807 --> 00:27:48,207
But didn't Kang Yeon Ja's French
sound amazing?

462
00:27:48,412 --> 00:27:51,002
- It sounded just like a native speaker.
- Jeong Ran!

463
00:27:52,540 --> 00:27:53,639
What's gotten into you?

464
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:10,560
Honey.

465
00:28:26,505 --> 00:28:28,373
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
